Class Fraction

  • java.lang.Object
    • Fraction
  • public class Fraction
extends java.lang.Object
    A class representing a fraction of integer values. The class provides functionality for simplifying fractions, and performing basic fraction computations.
    Author:
    Norm Krumpe

      • Fraction

        public Fraction​(java.lang.String fractionString)
        Constructs a fraction by extracting the numerator and denominator from a /-separated pair of integers. For example, given the String "4/17", the numerator would be 4 and the denominator would be 17. *
        Parameters:
        fractionString - a string, such a 3/4, containing two int values, separated by a slash

      • fixSigns

        public void fixSigns()
        Simplifies the signs of this fraction's numerator and denominator. If both signs are negative, then the signs are dropped. If one sign is positive and the other is negative, the negative will be moved to the numerator. If the denominator is 0, no change is made to the signs.

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        Returns a String representation of this fraction in the form "a/b"
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        a /-separated pair of integers representing this fraction.

      • simplify

        public void simplify()
        Changes this fraction's numerator and denominator so that it is in "lowest terms" (sometimes referred to as a "common fraction". This includes fixing the signs. For example, if a fraction is 24/-18, this method will change it to -3/2.

      • toDouble

        public double toDouble()
        Computes this fractions decimal value. For example, if the fraction is -3/4, then this method would return -0.75.
        Returns:
        the decimal value equivalent to this fraction

      • getReciprocal

        public Fraction getReciprocal()
        Returns a new fraction that is the reciprocal of this fraction. Does not modify this fraction.
        Returns:
        a fraction whose numerator and denominator are the denominator and numerator of this fraction.

      • toPrettyString

        public java.lang.String toPrettyString()
        Returns a 3-line representation of this fraction, with its numerator on the first line, its denominator on the last line, and a "fraction bar" made of hyphens as the separator. The length of the fraction bar is 2 more than the length of the longer number, and the numerator and denominator are centered above and below that bar, as much as possible.
        Returns:
        a 3-line String representation of the fraction.
